Description: Complete seal-impression with the impressions of a wooden flat object at the rear that showed a threat along it. Perpendicular two impressions of a turned string. The fine brown Nile clay has few inclusions of mica and was hardened after excavation without proper cleaning. There are some small cracks on the surface as well as blackening from fire. The front is slightly rounded and covered by finger prints, in the centre an impression of a seal that looks like it originates from a ring bezel. The seal shows a cartouche with two seated deities facing each other (Ptah and Ma'at), mr n Htp [Hr]: name of Horemheb: Mrj-n-Pth Htp-Hr-Ma'at.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), E14.7 temple magazine
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
